--- full rules for this game ---
The goal of the game is to be the first player to build and launch their rocket.
Each player starts with 5 points. Points can increase and decrease as the game progresses, but cannot be negative.
The game ends when a player successfully launches their rocket.

Players gain and lose points by playing cards. Different types of cards increase/decrease points differently and may affect other players.

There are 4 types of cards:
-- Progress card: The Player who plays it gains points (6-10 points).
-- Nuclear Scare card: All players lose points (4-6 points).
-- Sabotage card: Only drawn from the damage deck, the player who draws it loses points (1-4 points).
-- Freeze card: Freezes another player for one turn. Also reduces the other Player's points (by 4-6 points) The Player who plays it also gains points (1-2 points).
-- Spy card: The Player who plays it steals a card from another Player and places it in their hand. Costs 1 point to play.

Players start with 3 random cards in hand. The remaining cards start in two decks:
-- the Mixed Deck that contains a mixture of all card types
-- the Damage Deck that contains a mixture of only cards that can do damage

Each turn, a Player can choose one of 3 options:
-- 1. Play a card from their hand
-- 2. Draw a random card from the Mixed Deck. They do not get to play it.
-- 3. Draw a random card from the Damage Deck. They must play it immediately, and they do not gain points from playing it, but other Players lose points.

If a player crosses one of three checkpoints, they have the option to test their rocket.
The final checkpoint is the rocket launch.  If any test/launch is unsuccessful, the player is pushed back to the start of the phase.
Choosing to skip a rocket test will increase your chances of failure in proceeding tests/launches.


